 strength. Analysing members’ efforts in fields such as science, journalism, the arts, broadcasting, and education, The Chronology of Revolution offers an alternative, radical history of Britain between 1920 and 1991 which draws out important lessons for the contemporary Left.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCommunismzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical partieszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aAntonio Gramsci.  aBritish Communism.  aBritish Labour Party.  aCPGB.  aCommunist Party of Great Britain.  aactivism.  aarchival research.  acivil society.  aculture.  ahistoriography.  arevolution.  asocialism.  asocialist strategy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753615240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487536152423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487536152.jpg  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles